And I do think he believed her this time.

04:48.000 --> 04:53.000
Yeah, I think he was understanding when he said,

04:53.000 --> 04:55.000
okay, then try and get some rest.

04:55.000 --> 04:57.000
Yeah, and Julie sounded pretty sick.

04:57.000 --> 04:58.000
Yes, yes, she did.

04:58.000 --> 05:00.000
Yeah, it was convincing.

05:00.000 --> 05:02.000
Well, you know what?

05:02.000 --> 05:05.000
I almost called in sick last week.

05:05.000 --> 05:06.000
Really?

05:06.000 --> 05:11.000
Yeah, I wasn't feeling very well, and so I almost didn't come to work.

05:11.000 --> 05:14.000
Oh, that would have been really bad for me.

05:14.000 --> 05:16.000
I would have been stuck here without you, Marco.

05:16.000 --> 05:19.000
Yeah, you would have had to do the podcast all by yourself.

05:19.000 --> 05:20.000
Oh, no.

05:20.000 --> 05:25.000
You know, actually, I had the same symptoms as Julie.

05:25.000 --> 05:29.000
I also had a headache, and I had a sore throat,

05:29.000 --> 05:33.000
and also the worst thing and the thing that I hate the most

05:33.000 --> 05:35.000
is I had a runny nose.

05:35.000 --> 05:39.000
That's really bad, because then you have to blow your nose all the time,

05:39.000 --> 05:42.000
and then it gets red, and it hurts, right?

05:42.000 --> 05:43.000
Exactly, yeah.

05:43.000 --> 05:46.000
Luckily, I didn't have a fever, though.

05:46.000 --> 05:47.000
Oh, thank God.

05:47.000 --> 05:51.000
So did you take some medicine, and it just killed everything?

05:51.000 --> 05:56.000
Yeah, I had a friend, and he had some pills for the flu,

05:56.000 --> 06:00.000
and he just gave me a couple, and I felt better in about two days.

06:00.000 --> 06:01.000
Oh, great.

06:01.000 --> 06:05.000
Well, so guys, let me tell you about a very funny thing

06:05.000 --> 06:09.000
